From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: V5 Project <v5@example.invalid>
Date: Sat, 16 May 2026 13:12:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] v5: relax generic frame timeout

The V5 board currently uses the IgH generic Ethernet backend on the Zynq
GEM path. LinuxCNC/lcec owns cyclic motion natively, but frame responses can
arrive later than the upstream 500 us datagram timeout during startup state
transitions. When that happens the master marks a valid late frame as timed
out and then treats the response as unmatched, preventing the slaves from
reaching OP.

Keep the native LinuxCNC EtherCAT path and relax only the frame timeout for
this board profile.
---
 master/globals.h | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/master/globals.h b/master/globals.h
index 1111111..2222222 100644
--- a/master/globals.h
+++ b/master/globals.h
@@
 /** Datagram timeout in microseconds. */
-#define EC_IO_TIMEOUT 500
+#define EC_IO_TIMEOUT 5000
-- 
